[1 vouwblad, 3 bladen] [vouwblad, recto] Bruegel. V&A. Catalogue of the Celebrated Collection of Works of Art and Vertu, known as “The Vienna Museum,” the property of Messrs. Löwenstein, Brothers ... which will be sold by auction, by Messrs. Christie, Manson & Woods, March 12, 1860, and nine following days, [London : W. Clowes & Sons, 1860] [...]; [vouwblad, verso] Lot 1291 [...], Pictures, 1070 Brueghel -A village scene, with numerous figures; 1086 Interior of a picture gallery; [blad 1, recto] Rudolf II - Bruegel [Johann J.H.] Czikann - [Franz] Graeffer, Oesterreichische National-Encyclopedie, Bd. IV, Wien 1836, citaten pp. 579, 711, 713; [blad 2, recto] 'Ungetreue Hirt.' [Theodor von] Frimmel citaten pp. 117, 203, 532; [blad 3, recto] In der Slg. des Kaisers Rudolf Prag: "ein Schafhirt vom alten Peeter (jetzt vielleicht in Wien)"; Frimmel, Galeriestudien. Gesch.d.Wiener Gemälde Slgen, [Leipzig: Meyer], I/1 1898/99 (Gesch. der kaiserl. Gemäldegalerie), p. 110; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Wohl eher der 'Ungetreure Hirte.'
